+## Findings
+1. [P1] Fix 1 regression still present in programmatic sheet close — `popOverlay()` still calls `window.history.back()` whenever the close did not originate from `popstate` ([C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1306](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L1306)). The table-code sheet’s programmatic close path still uses that helper ([C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3494](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3494)), and the `popstate` handler then closes whatever overlay is now on top of the ref stack ([C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L2374](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L2374)). With `cart -> tableConfirm` open, swiping or tapping `×` on `tableConfirm` still removes `tableConfirm` from the stack first, then `history.back()` closes `cart`. FIX: add the requested `isProgrammaticCloseRef`, set it before consuming the sheet’s own history entry, and make the `popstate` listener skip one cycle when that flag is set so only `tableConfirm` is removed.
+2. [P2] Fix 2 is still incomplete against the task contract — the custom toast now renders as a fixed chip ([C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L376](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L376)), but it still uses fallback copy `Добавлено` instead of `Добавлено в корзину` ([C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L378](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L378)), dismisses after 1500ms instead of about 2000ms ([C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L58](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L58)), and stays at `z-50`, below the `z-[60]` confirmation sheet in `x.jsx`. FIX: change the fallback text to `t('menu.added_to_cart', 'Добавлено в корзину')`, increase the timeout to about 2s, and raise the toast container to a guaranteed top layer such as `z-[200]`.
+3. [P2] Fix 3 restores the CTA text, but the dialog button still does not enforce the required 44px mobile target — the dish detail action now has visible text ([C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3699](C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx#L3699)), yet its class is only `w-full text-white` and does not add `min-h-[44px]` or `h-11`. In this page file, other buttons explicitly add `min-h-[44px]` when that requirement matters, so this path still relies on shared defaults instead of guaranteeing the accepted touch size. FIX: add `min-h-[44px]` or `h-11` to the dish detail CTA while keeping the existing `t('menu.add_to_cart', 'Добавить в корзину')` text and white foreground.
